cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI

The paper discusses the instability and variance of neural predictive algorithms in large datasets, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on the use of word2vec in a recommender system, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the influence of single data points, which relates to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and the need to detect differences in informational value of data points on a large scale, which relates to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
